<TITLE> '586MW since 2009' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  The government has added an additional 586MW of electricity to the national grid since it took office, the finance minister told parliament Sunday. Of the 15 installed plants, one but all  a 120MW Shiddhirganj unit  were from the private sector initiatives. "We have taken up immediate, short-, mid- and long-term plans for production and expansion of electricity," said Muhith. According to that, projects were under way to generate 732MW by the end of this year. The long-term plan envisions that 920MW will be added by 2011, 1369MW by 2012, 1975MW by 2013, 1770MW by 2014 and 2600MW by 2015. This would add 9276MW by 2015. The evaluation of a tender for a 530MW rental power plant is in process under the government's short-term plan to build 1,500MW rental power plants, according to the minister. Presenting the 'Budget 2009-10: Implementation Status and Macroeconomic Analysis report for the Third Quarter (July-March)' in parliament, Muhith said that ten peaking power plants with a capacity of 820MW were in the pipeline. bd
